cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.CYBER, cs.DB 

The paper focuses on understanding social network structure and evolution, which falls under the scope of both cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). The paper also discusses the use of data and modeling techniques, which could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper touches on the topic of defenses against Sybil attacks, which could be classified under cs.CYBER (Computer Security and Cryptography).
